Additional Notes

While researching these 10 creators, I noticed a common pattern: most of them combine personal storytelling with practical frameworks rather than just giving generic tips. 
This made it easier to identify genuine experts versus people who simply repost popular advice.

I also noticed that creators who are solo founders (like Simon Hoiberg, Marc Lou, and Jonathan Rintala) tend to be more transparent with numbers and experiments, while larger channels (like SaaStr) provide more structured, 
conference-style content from multiple speakers.

This mix gave a good balance between personal, practical advice and broader industry frameworks.
